title.rendered: UP vs Gujarat, India Women’s League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

UP: Alyssa Healy (c & wk), Shweta Sehrawat, Tahlia McGrath, Deepti Sharma, Devika Vaidya/Kiran Navgire, Sophie Ecclestone, Grace Harris/Lauren Bell, Simran Shaikh, Rajeshwari Gayakwad, Shabnim Ismail, Anjali Sarvani

Beth Mooney is in doubt for this clash. If she doesn’t take the field, Sneh Rana is likely to lead Gujarat.

Gujarat: Beth Mooney (c & wk)/Sophia Dunkley, Sabbhineni Meghana, Harleen Deol, Ashleigh Gardner, Annabel Sutherland, Dayalan Hemalatha, Georgia Wareham, Sneh Rana, Tanuja Kanwar, Mansi Joshi, Monica Patel

Venue: Dr DY Patil Sports Academy, Mumbai

Pitch Type: Good for batting

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Shweta Sehrawat was the top run-scorer in the U-19 T20 World Cup 2023. Despite maintaining a high strike rate of 139, she slammed 297 runs at a colossal average of 99.

Sophie Ecclestone hasn’t gone wicketless in the format for six consecutive games and has bagged four three-fors in the process.

Alyssa Healy has added 379 runs at 24, including the highest score of 90, in India. At DY Patil Sports Academy, she has added 62 runs in two innings.

In India, Tahlia McGrath averages an impressive 49 with the bat. In her only two outings at DY Patil Sports Academy, she registered scores of 70* and 40*.

Kiran Navgire has all the ammunition to rapidly pile on runs. In the 2022 Women’s Challenger, she collected 69 runs at a smashing strike rate of 147 in two innings.

Thanks to her all-round skills, Ashleigh Gardner has featured in the Best11 in four of her last five outings.

Although Gujarat got bundled out for 64 against Mumbai, Dayalan Hemalatha was impressive by being the top run-getter (29 off 23). She could move up the order in Beth’s absence.

Beth Mooney has clobbered three fifties in her last four innings. In India she averages an impressive 49, including the highest score of 89* in T20Is.

For five consecutive games, Monica Patel has gone wicketless.
